Cell["\<\
Comparing part (a) to part (b), the event that the first two are increasing \
stations is more specific than the event that at least two in the sample are \
increasing, and it is more favorable to the event of at least 3 increases. \
There is no reason to suspect that the conditional probabilities would come \
out equal.  In the latter case, there are still many more remaining outcomes \
in the reduced sample space, which serves to lower the conditional \
probability.  \[FilledSquare]\
\>", "Text",
