Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Bayes' Formula", "Subsection",
 FontWeight->"Bold"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tThe law of total probability can also be used easily to derive an \
important formula called ",
 StyleBox["Bayes' Formula",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ".  The setting is as above, in which a collection of events ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["A", "1"], ",", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["A", "2"], ",", " ", "...", " ", ",", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["A", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]]],
 " partitions \[CapitalOmega].  Then P[",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "] can be expressed in terms of the conditional probabilities P[",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " | ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["A", "i"], TraditionalForm]]],
 "], which we suppose  are known. The question we want to consider now is: is \
it possible to reverse these conditional probabilities to find P[",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["A", "i"], TraditionalForm]]],
 " | ",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "] for any ",
 StyleBox["i",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 1, 2, ..., ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "?  The importance of being able to do so is illustrated by the next \
example.  Roughly the idea is that diagnostic tools such as lie detectors, \
medical procedures, etc. can be pre-tested on subjects who are known to have \
a condition, so that the probability that they give a correct diagnosis can \
be estimated.  But we really want to use the diagnostic test later on unknown \
individuals and conclude something about whether the individual has the \
condition given a positive test result. In the pre-testing phase the event \
being conditioned on is that the individual has the condition, but in the \
usage phase we know whether or not the test is positive, so the order of \
conditioning is being reversed. \n\tAll we need to derive ",
 StyleBox["Bayes' formula",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", which is (6) below, is the definition of the conditional probability ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"P", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["A", "i"], " ", "|", " ", "B"}], "]"}], " "}], 
   TraditionalForm]]],
 "and the law of total probability: "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.42391383478125*^9, 3.423913976640625*^9}, {
  3.423928014109375*^9, 3.42392814196875*^9}, {3.423928267234375*^9, 
  3.423928292484375*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["P",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox[
      SubscriptBox["A", "i"],
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "|", 
     StyleBox[" ",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["B",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "]"}], " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["P",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["A",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "i"], "\[Intersection]", 
       StyleBox["B",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "]"}], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["P",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
      StyleBox["B",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "]"}]], "=", " ", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["P",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["B",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", "|", " ", 
        StyleBox[
         SubscriptBox["A", "i"],
         FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["P",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
       StyleBox[
        SubscriptBox["A", "i"],
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "]"}]}], 
     RowBox[{" ", 
      FormBox[
       RowBox[{
        UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
         RowBox[{"j", "=", "1"}], "n"], 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["P",
          FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
         RowBox[{"B", "|", 
          SubscriptBox["A", "j"]}], "]"}], 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["P",
          FontSlant->"Plain"], "[", 
         SubscriptBox["A", "j"], "]"}]}],
       TraditionalForm]}]]}]}], TextForm]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.42392815225*^9, 3.423928241890625*^9}}],

Cell["We close the section with a nice application.", "Text"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Example 4",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "  As of 2006, the Centers for Disease Control estimate of the number of \
people in the U.S. who were infected with the HIV virus was around 1.1 \
million among a total population of about 300 million, which is a proportion \
of about ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = .0037. In considering policy issues like the institution of universal \
HIV screening, one must be aware of the possibility of needlessly frightening \
uninfected people with a positive screening result. Also, a person with a \
positive screening result could then be subjected unnecessarily to further \
costly, time-consuming, but more accurate diagnostic procedures to confirm \
the condition.  Suppose for our example that a screening procedure is \
accurate at a level ",
 StyleBox["q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (near 1) for people who do have HIV, and it gives an incorrect positive \
test with probability ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (near 0), for people who do not have HIV.  If a randomly selected \
individual has a positive screening result, what is the probability that this \
person actually has HIV?  If the screening could be redesigned to improve \
performance, which would be the most important quantity to improve:  ",
 StyleBox["q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " or ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "? \n\tWe introduce the following notation, suggested by the problem \
statement:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.423914019203125*^9, 3.423914026390625*^9}, {
  3.42393091084375*^9, 3.423930914765625*^9}, {3.423931134265625*^9, 
  3.42393117625*^9}, {3.42393128871875*^9, 3.4239313758125*^9}, {
  3.4239320348125*^9, 3.423932060234375*^9}, {3.42393219090625*^9, 
  3.42393219753125*^9}, {3.423932239640625*^9, 3.423932240125*^9}, {
  3.4239322750625*^9, 3.423932280890625*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["p",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"P", "[", 
   RowBox[{
   "randomly", " ", "selected", " ", "person", " ", "has", " ", "HIV"}], 
   "]"}]}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["q",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"P", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"test", " ", "positive"}], " ", "|", " ", 
    RowBox[{"person", " ", "has", " ", "HIV"}]}], "]"}]}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["r",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"P", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"test", " ", "positive"}], " ", "|", " ", 
    RowBox[{"person", " ", "does", " ", "not", " ", "have", " ", "HIV"}]}], 
   "]"}]}]}], "Equation",
 FontFamily->"Times New Roman"],

Cell["By Bayes' formula,", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"P", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"person", " ", "has", " ", "HIV"}], " ", "|", " ", 
    RowBox[{"test", " ", "positive"}]}], "]"}], " ", 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontColor->GrayLevel[0]], 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"P", "[", 
       RowBox[{
       "person", " ", "has", " ", "HIV", " ", "and", " ", "test", " ", 
        "positive"}], "]"}], " "}], 
     RowBox[{"P", "[", 
      RowBox[{"test", " ", "positive"}], "]"}]],
    FontColor->GrayLevel[0]], "=", " ", 
   FormBox[
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"q", "\[CenterDot]", "p"}], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"q", "\[CenterDot]", "p"}], "+", 
      RowBox[{"r", "(", 
       RowBox[{"1", "-", "p"}], ")"}]}]],
    TraditionalForm]}]}]], "Equation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.423914110046875*^9, 3.42391414425*^9}},
 FontFamily->"Times New Roman"],

